<div id="review_86426334" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/86426334" />
    <a title="K.D. Absolutely" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2156200-k-d-absolutely"><img alt="K.D. Absolutely" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1471967140p2/2156200.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/86426334?book_show_action=true">Jan 23, 2010</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="K.D. Absolutely" class="user" itemprop="url" name="K.D. Absolutely" href="/user/show/2156200-k-d-absolutely">K.D. Absolutely</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>


          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">Tata J</span></div>

          <div>
    <span class="greyText">Recommended to K.D. by: </span>
      1001 Books You Must Read Before You Die
  </div>


          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2156200-k-d-absolutely?shelf=booker">booker</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2156200-k-d-absolutely?shelf=ex-1001">ex-1001</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer86426334" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10981370431061264101">This is the first novel of J. M. Coetzee after he won the 2003 Nobel Prize for Literature. This 264-page novel is another proof that he deserved all the praises bestowed to him including the only novelist who won Booker Prize twice.<br/><br/>Up to around 240+ pages the novel was so strong that I would not mind giving it a 5-star rating. It has unbelievable characters for a very simple plot: a 60-year old guy divorcee who lost his right leg and thought of having an instant family via his caretaker. Coetzee</span>
  <span id="freeText10981370431061264101" style="display:none">This is the first novel of J. M. Coetzee after he won the 2003 Nobel Prize for Literature. This 264-page novel is another proof that he deserved all the praises bestowed to him including the only novelist who won Booker Prize twice.<br /><br />Up to around 240+ pages the novel was so strong that I would not mind giving it a 5-star rating. It has unbelievable characters for a very simple plot: a 60-year old guy divorcee who lost his right leg and thought of having an instant family via his caretaker. Coetzee has that flair in making his characters behave and speak unbelievably: you would not know what will they say the moment they start moving their lips. Brilliant thoughts. Mesmerizing vocabular. Thought-provoking insights.<br /><br />The only reason why I am not giving this a 4 or 5 star is the disappointing ending. The last 20 pages seem to be hurried. I just had that feeling that J. M. Coetzee just wanted to close the story by delivering the moral lesson: not to be too quick in judging people. Nice reminder there but too simple for a very beautiful well-developed plot and memorable characters.<br /><br />This is my 3rd novel by J. M. Coetzee and I am looking forward to reading more.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10981370431061264101" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


