        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2112003779" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer18374681999704641429">Paul, riding his bike is hit by a car, and his leg takes the brunt of the crash. The doctors have to amputate, and Paul refuses to have a prosthesis. I had tried to read this book years ago, but I wasn&apos;t able to get through it. Even this time, I felt I had to force myself to finish it. One of the reviewers thought that this book was magical realism, and I see the point. <br/>While Paul is recovering he requires a lot of in home care. Paul falls in love with his nurse, and a woman named Elizabeth Cost</span>
  <span id="freeText18374681999704641429" style="display:none">Paul, riding his bike is hit by a car, and his leg takes the brunt of the crash. The doctors have to amputate, and Paul refuses to have a prosthesis. I had tried to read this book years ago, but I wasn't able to get through it. Even this time, I felt I had to force myself to finish it. One of the reviewers thought that this book was magical realism, and I see the point. <br />While Paul is recovering he requires a lot of in home care. Paul falls in love with his nurse, and a woman named Elizabeth Costello walks in on his life off the street, begins orchestrating his life. <br /><br /></span>
