        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3774199774" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer14409493804165112987">A pretty harrowing (mainly in the sense of toe-cringing) examination of themes such as growing old (and weak), caring love vs. passion, action vs. inaction, and in particular male pride and vanity. in many ways it was just down my alley, so my 4 stars are very big indeed.<br/><br/>Maybe having read ‘Elizabeth Costello’ (who plays a significant role here) would have added the last star? <br/><br/></span>

          </span>
        </div>


